**Immortal** | Solo Power - Nightmare Team | Haunted
__Basics__
The Immortal cannot die by any means, but will be banished if they are elected as Mayor. Each night they can choose to have a voting power of 1, 2, or 3 for the following day.
__Details__
When the Immortal is elected as Mayor, they are instead immediately banished and eliminated from the game.
All Nightmare Team members share a channel for communication.
Choosing a voting power is an end night action.
The Immortal is a member of the nightmare team and purgatory channel. The nightmare team wins when all other players are dead or unaligned.
If there is no reaper, the Immortal may choose to become a reaper.

__Simplified__
The Immortal cannot die by any means, unless they are elected Mayor. Each night they can choose to have a voting power of 1, 2, or 3 for the following day.
When The Immortal dies from becoming Mayor, they do not become a ghost, they are instead immediately banished.
If there is no reaper, the Immortal may choose to become a reaper.

__Formalized__
Haunted Role
Starting: Protect @Self from `All` through Passive Defense (~Permanent)
End Night: Manipulate @Self's `public voting power` to @Selection (~NextDay) [Condition: (@Selection > 0) and (@Selection < 4)] |immortal.1|
On Poll `Election` Win:
  • True Kill @Self
  • True Banish @Self
Immediate: Role Change @Self to `Reaper` [Condition: not (@(Role:Reaper) exists)] |immortal.2|

__Card__
The Immortal cooperates with the Reaper so that they will never go to the afterlife.
